  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Emergency Response and Assistance to Displaced Populations in Niger</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Building on its earlier responses to humanitarian needs in the Sahel crisis (regions of Tillabery and Tahoua), Maradi and Lake Chad Basin crisis (region of Diffa), specifically through earlier projects funded by the United States&#x2019; Department of State Bureau for Population, Refugees and Migrants Migration, the following intervention focuses on two key outcomes. Crisis-affected populations in Diffa, Maradi and Tahoua have access to adequate and dignified humanitarian assistance in response to forced movement and to improved protection assistance to simultaneously alleviate some of the most pressing humanitarian needs faced by crisis-affected populations, including addressing protection needs while building on their resilience and work with the Government of Niger towards identifying durable solutions to long-term displaced populations.</narrative>
  </description>
